HEADWORD: Obelion
<hw>O*be"li*on</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., from Gr.
<grk>'obelo`s</grk> a spit.]</ety> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The region of
the skull between the two parietal foramina where the closure of the
sagittal suture usually begins.</def>⟦br⟧
